<p><strong>Note: </strong>You will need to set up your WooCommerce store before starting this tutorial. If you don&#8217;t have one yet, then please see our <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/woocommerce-tutorial-ultimate-guide/" title="WooCommerce Made Simple: A Step-by-Step Tutorial [+ Resources]">complete WooCommerce guide for beginners</a>.</p>

</div>


<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-1">üõ†Ô∏è Step 1: Set Up Your Amazon MCF Account</h4>



<p>Before you can connect Amazon to your WooCommerce store, you need to make sure your Amazon FBA account is properly set up. </p>



<p>First, you‚Äôll need to have a Professional Seller account on Amazon. If you don&#8217;t already have one, head over to <a href="https://sellercentral.amazon.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Amazon Seller Central">sellercentral.amazon.com</a> to sign up.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="332" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sign-up-for-amazon-seller-account.png" alt="Sign up for an Amazon Seller account" class="wp-image-353308" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sign-up-for-amazon-seller-account.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sign-up-for-amazon-seller-account-300x146.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>üö®<strong>Important:</strong>&nbsp;You must sign up for a&nbsp;Professional Seller account. The Individual plan does not support the necessary tools for this integration.</p>

</div>


<p>Once you enter your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address-in-5-minutes-step-by-step/" title="How to Create a Free Business Email Address (in Just 5 Minutes)">email address</a> and create a password, Amazon will send you a verification code. This is just to make sure your email is valid. </p>



<p>After you enter the correct code, Amazon will take you to the next screen and outline the steps needed to complete your account setup.</p>



<p>Make sure you have the following documents ready:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>A valid government-issued ID (like a passport or driver‚Äôs license)</li>



<li>A recent bank account or credit card statement</li>



<li>A chargeable credit card</li>



<li>Your mobile phone</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="334" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/amazon-seller-account-requirements.png" alt="Amazon seller account requirements" class="wp-image-353309" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/amazon-seller-account-requirements.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/amazon-seller-account-requirements-300x147.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Amazon will then ask for your<a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-properly-add-your-business-address-in-wordpress/" title="How to Properly Add Your Business Address in WordPress"> business location</a> and business type.</p>



<p>Be sure to select the country where your business is located because Amazon will verify it later.</p>



<p>For business type, you can choose from several options such as State-owned business, Publicly-owned business, Privately-owned business, Charity, or &#8216;None, I am an individual.&#8217; </p>



<p>If you haven‚Äôt officially registered your business yet, just select the last option. You‚Äôll also need to enter your full name and click &#8216;Agree and continue.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="375" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-business-location-and-type.png" alt="Add business location and type" class="wp-image-353310" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-business-location-and-type.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-business-location-and-type-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the next step, you need to give your personal information, including a form of identification (either your passport number or driver‚Äôs license number). </p>



<p>After that, you‚Äôll be asked to verify your mobile phone number by entering a PIN code that Amazon sends via text or call. </p>



<p>Once you enter the code correctly, your phone number will be verified. When everything looks good, click &#8216;Next&#8217; to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="346" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-personal-information.png" alt="Add personal information" class="wp-image-353311" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-personal-information.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-personal-information-300x153.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Now you‚Äôll be asked for your billing information. This includes a valid credit card and bank account number. </p>



<p>Amazon needs this to charge your monthly fees and deposit your earnings from sales.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="308" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/provide-bank-info.png" alt="Provide bank information" class="wp-image-353312" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/provide-bank-info.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/provide-bank-info-300x136.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once your billing info is verified, you‚Äôll move on to a few questions about your products and your Amazon store. Don‚Äôt worry ‚Äî you don‚Äôt need to overthink this part. </p>



<p>You‚Äôll be asked to enter a name for your Amazon store (you can change it later), and answer a few product-related questions, like:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Do you have UPC codes for your products?</li>



<li>Do you have any diversity certifications?</li>



<li>Are you the manufacturer or brand owner?</li>



<li>Do you have a government-registered trademark?</li>
</ul>



<p>Answer these based on your situation, and click &#8216;Next.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="341" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/answer-store-related-questions.png" alt="Answer store related questions" class="wp-image-353313" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/answer-store-related-questions.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/answer-store-related-questions-300x150.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>At this point, you‚Äôll need to upload your ID (like a passport or license) and a bank statement to verify your identity. Once submitted, Amazon will ask you to complete a video call with one of its associates.</p>



<p>This required video call helps Amazon verify your identity by matching your face to the documents you submitted.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="384" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/identity-and-address-verification-1.png" alt="Identity and address verification" class="wp-image-353315" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/identity-and-address-verification-1.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/identity-and-address-verification-1-300x169.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After the video call and final review, your account will be approved, and you‚Äôll be able to log in to your Amazon Seller Central dashboard.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-create-an-fba-product-listing-for-your-woocommerce-product">üìÑ Step 2: Create an FBA Product Listing for Your WooCommerce Products</h4>



<p>Now that your Amazon Seller account is ready, it‚Äôs time to set up the actual product listings that Amazon will fulfill.</p>



<p>For every product you want Amazon to ship, you&#8217;ll need to create a matching product listing in your Amazon Seller Central account.</p>



<p>To do this, log in to the Seller Central dashboard and head over to the <strong>Catalogue ¬ª Add Product</strong> page. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="373" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/visit-add-products-page-on-seller-account-dashboard.png" alt="Visit the Add Products page on the seller account dashboard" class="wp-image-353316" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/visit-add-products-page-on-seller-account-dashboard.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/visit-add-products-page-on-seller-account-dashboard-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>If your product already exists on Amazon, you can match it.</p>



<p>But if it‚Äôs unique to your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-start-an-online-store/" title="How to Start an Online Store (Step by Step for Beginners)">online store</a>, you‚Äôll need to create a new listing by entering all the details manually.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>üí°<strong>Quick Tip:</strong>&nbsp;It‚Äôs usually best to create a new listing for your brand. This gives you full control over the product title, images, and description. If you match an existing listing, you‚Äôll be selling on a product page that someone else controls.</p>

</div>


<p>Then, click the &#8216;Sell this product&#8217; button. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="318" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-product-details.png" alt="Add product details" class="wp-image-353317" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-product-details.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/add-product-details-300x140.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will direct you to a new screen where you‚Äôll just need to enter basic details like quantity, price, and fulfillment channel. </p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-blue">

<p>üí°<strong>Just one quick note:</strong> Amazon assigns each product a Seller SKU, which you‚Äôll need later to match with your WooCommerce product. I recommend copying these into a spreadsheet so that you can easily access them later.</p>



<p>Think of the SKU as a product‚Äôs secret code ‚Äî WooCommerce and Amazon must use the exact same code so the plugin knows which item to ship.</p>



<p>For example, if your product&#8217;s SKU is&nbsp;<code>TSHIRT-BLUE-LG</code>&nbsp;in WooCommerce, you must enter&nbsp;<code>TSHIRT-BLUE-LG</code>&nbsp;as the Seller SKU in your Amazon listing for the connection to work.</p>

</div>


<p>For FBA, be sure to choose &#8216;Amazon will ship and provide customer service for this product.&#8217; This tells Amazon to handle the product using FBA instead of making you ship it yourself.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="264" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-fullfilment-channel-details.png" alt="Configure fulfillment channel details " class="wp-image-353318" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-fullfilment-channel-details.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-fullfilment-channel-details-300x116.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once the listing is complete, save it and repeat the process for other products on your website.</p>



<p>You‚Äôll now be able to send that product‚Äôs inventory to Amazon and make it eligible for both FBA and Multi-Channel Fulfillment (MCF) ‚Äî which means Amazon can ship it when an order comes from your WooCommerce store.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-3-send-your-inventory-to-amazon-using-send-to-amazon">üì¶ Step 3: Send Your Inventory to Amazon Using ‚ÄúSend to Amazon‚Äù</h4>



<p>Once your product is listed in Amazon Seller Central and marked for FBA, the next step is to send your inventory to Amazon‚Äôs warehouse. </p>



<p>This is how your WooCommerce product becomes eligible for multi-channel fulfillment.</p>



<p>To do this, you‚Äôll use Amazon‚Äôs Send to Amazon shipment workflow, which replaces the old shipping process with a more streamlined system. </p>



<p>Amazon will inform you which fulfillment center(s) to ship to and may request that you split your shipment across multiple locations to help distribute inventory throughout their network.</p>



<p>Start by going to your <strong>Manage All Inventory</strong> page in Seller Central. </p>



<p>Here, find the product you want to ship and click the &#8216;Edit&#8217; dropdown next to it. Then, select the  &#8216;Send/Replenish Inventory&#8217; option. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="306" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-send-replenish-inventory.png" alt="Click the Send/Replenish Inventory button" class="wp-image-353333" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-send-replenish-inventory.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-send-replenish-inventory-300x135.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open the Send to Amazon setup, where the platform will ask for your packing details.</p>



<p>You‚Äôll need to enter the number of units you‚Äôre placing in each box, the box dimensions and weight, and whether Amazon or you will apply the product labels.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="351" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-packing-details.png" alt="Configure packing details" class="wp-image-353336" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-packing-details.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-packing-details-300x155.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You can save this as a template if you plan to use the same box setup again later. </p>



<p>Once that‚Äôs done, enter the number of units you want to send, then click &#8216;Ready to Send&#8217; followed by &#8216;Confirm and Continue.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="181" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-ready-to-send.png" alt="Click the Ready to Send button" class="wp-image-353339" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-ready-to-send.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/click-ready-to-send-300x80.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Next, you‚Äôll choose your shipping method. Most WooCommerce sellers use Small Parcel Delivery (SPD) for individual boxes, especially if you‚Äôre using Amazon‚Äôs partnered carrier, like UPS. </p>



<p>You can also go with Less Than Truckload (LTL) if you‚Äôre shipping pallets. Amazon will show you rate options for each. </p>



<p>After choosing your ship date and carrier, click the &#8216;Accept charges and confirm shipping&#8217;  button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="329" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-shipping-mode.png" alt="Choose a shipping mode" class="wp-image-353341" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-shipping-mode.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-shipping-mode-300x145.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Now it‚Äôs time to print your shipping labels and add them to the boxes you plan to ship. You can then drop off the boxes at UPS or schedule a pickup.</p>



<p>Once your inventory is live, you&#8217;re ready to connect your WooCommerce store to Amazon FBA.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-4-connect-woocommerce-to-amazon-fba-using-the-never-settle-plugin">üîß Step 4: Connect WooCommerce to Amazon FBA Using a Plugin</h4>



<p>Now that your inventory is active in Amazon FBA, you can connect your WooCommerce store to Amazon using the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/woocommerce-amazon-fulfillment-mcf-for-woocommerce/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="WooCommerce Amazon Fulfillment (MCF) for WooCommerce">Amazon Fulfillment for WooCommerce</a> plugin. </p>



<p>This tool allows orders from your WooCommerce store to be automatically fulfilled by Amazon without you having to manually ship anything.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-set-up-the-amazon-fulfillment-for-woocommerce-plugin">Set Up the Amazon Fulfillment for WooCommerce Plugin</h5>



<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/woocommerce-amazon-fulfillment-mcf-for-woocommerce/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="WooCommerce Amazon Fulfillment (MCF) for WooCommerce">Amazon Fulfillment for WooCommerce</a> plugin. For step-by-step instructions, see our tutorial on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/" title="How to Install a WordPress Plugin ‚Äì Step by Step for Beginners">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>üö®<strong>Note: </strong>Amazon Fulfillment for WooCommerce is a premium plugin and doesn&#8217;t have a free version. However, out of all the tools that I have tested, it offers the most straightforward way to connect Amazon FBA to WooCommerce.</p>

</div>


<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-connect-to-your-amazon-seller-account">Connect to Your Amazon Seller Account</h5>



<p>Upon activation, visit the <strong>WooCommerce ¬ª Settings <strong>¬ª</strong> Integration <strong>¬ª</strong> Fulfillment by Amazon</strong> page from your WordPress dashboard to start the setup process.</p>



<p>Here, you‚Äôll first need to click the &#8216;Login With Amazon&#8217; button. This will direct you to a new screen where you have to add your Amazon Seller account credentials.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="269" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/login-with-amazon.png" alt="Login with Amazon" class="wp-image-354057" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/login-with-amazon.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/login-with-amazon-300x119.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After logging in, you‚Äôll return to the plugin settings, and your &#8216;Home Region&#8217; and &#8216;Marketplace ID&#8217; will be filled in automatically. </p>



<p>Now, you have to click the ‚ÄòClick to TEST Connection between Amazon and WooCommerce‚Äô button. This confirms that your website is linked to Amazon through the Selling Partner API.</p>



<p>An API (Application Programming Interface) is like a secure bridge that lets your WooCommerce store and Amazon talk to each other automatically.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="260" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/test-amazon-api-connection.png" alt="Test Amazon API connection with WooCommerce" class="wp-image-354222" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/test-amazon-api-connection.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/test-amazon-api-connection-300x115.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-import-your-amazon-products-into-woocommerce">Import Your Amazon Products into WooCommerce</h5>



<p>Once that is done, scroll down to the &#8216;Compare and Import Products from Amazon&#8217; section and click the &#8216;Compare &amp; Import your Products into WooCommerce by SKU&#8217; button. </p>



<p>This pulls product data directly from your Amazon catalog and matches it with your WooCommerce products based on SKU.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>üí°<strong>Bonus Tip: </strong>The SKUs in your WooCommerce store must match the ones in your Amazon inventory. Otherwise, the plugin won‚Äôt know which product to sync.</p>

</div>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="164" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-amazon-skus.png" alt="Check Amazon SKUs" class="wp-image-354223" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-amazon-skus.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-amazon-skus-300x72.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After that, go to the &#8216;Inventory (Stock Level) Settings&#8217; section. Here, you can click the &#8216;Click to Sync WooCommerce Stock Levels to match Amazon&#8217; button to update your inventory manually.</p>



<p>To make sure everything is syncing correctly, use the ‚ÄòTEST Inventory Connection‚Äô tool. </p>



<p>The plugin‚Äôs documentation may give a sample SKU (like OBRAMAIN) for testing, but I recommend using a real SKU from one of your own products. This will give you the most accurate test results.</p>



<p>If it works, your connection is good to go. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="199" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sync-woocommerce-and-amazon-stock-levels.png" alt="Sync WooCommerce and Amazon stock levels" class="wp-image-354224" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sync-woocommerce-and-amazon-stock-levels.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/sync-woocommerce-and-amazon-stock-levels-300x88.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Below that, I recommend enabling the ‚ÄòUpdate local stock levels per Order item sent to Amazon Fulfillment‚Äô setting. This will make sure your WooCommerce inventory automatically updates whenever a customer places an order.</p>



<p>You should also check the ‚ÄòAutomatically sync stock levels from Amazon at the interval below‚Äô box to enable automatic inventory syncing. </p>



<p>By default, the plugin syncs every 1440 minutes (once a day), but you can adjust this based on how often your stock changes.</p>



<p>There‚Äôs also an option to limit syncing to FBA-enabled products only, which can be helpful if you sell a mix of products fulfilled by Amazon and others that you ship yourself.</p>



<p>You can even set a low stock threshold so you get notified when items are running out. This helps <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-prevent-overselling-out-of-stock-items-in-wordpress/" title="How to Prevent Overselling Out of Stock Items in WordPress">prevent overselling</a> and keeps your store running smoothly.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="239" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-other-stock-level-settings.png" alt="Configure other stock level settings" class="wp-image-354225" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-other-stock-level-settings.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/configure-other-stock-level-settings-300x105.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-customize-order-fullfillment-settings">Customize Order Fulfillment Settings</h5>



<p>Once that is done, I suggest you add an ‚ÄòOrder Prefix‚Äô under the Order Fulfillment Settings.</p>



<p>It is a small label that will be added to Amazon-fulfilled orders in your dashboard. For example, you can use something like <code>fba</code> to make those orders easy to identify.</p>



<p>You can also customize the Order Comment (for example, ‚ÄúThank you for your order!‚Äù) and set a default shipping speed.</p>



<p>This default is used when a specific shipping method isn‚Äôt matched during checkout.</p>



<p>After that, make sure to check the &#8216;Enable Shipping Method Mapping&#8217; box. This step is really important because it connects the shipping options in your WooCommerce store to the actual shipping speeds Amazon offers, like Standard, Expedited, or Priority. </p>



<p>By turning this on, you‚Äôre telling the plugin to match the options your customers see at checkout with the correct delivery methods on Amazon‚Äôs side.</p>



<p>Finally, click the &#8216;Save Changes&#8217;  button to apply all your settings. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="245" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/enable-shipping-method-mapping.png" alt="Enable shipping method mapping" class="wp-image-354226" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/enable-shipping-method-mapping.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/enable-shipping-method-mapping-300x108.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-set-up-amazon-shipping">Set Up Amazon Shipping</h5>



<p>Now it‚Äôs time to configure Amazon shipping as a method within your WooCommerce store. This step ensures your customers can choose a shipping speed, and Amazon will know exactly how to fulfill it.</p>



<p>For this, head over to the <strong>Shipping</strong> tab on the WooCommerce Settings page, and either edit an existing shipping zone or create a new one. </p>



<p>Once you do that, click the &#8216;Add Shipping Method&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="212" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/woocommerce-add-shipping-method-min.png" alt="Adding a shipping method in WooCommerce" class="wp-image-325106" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/woocommerce-add-shipping-method-min.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/woocommerce-add-shipping-method-min-300x94.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open a popup, where you have to select &#8216;Amazon&#8217; as the shipping method.</p>



<p>Then, click the &#8216;Continue&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="338" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-amazon-as-the-shipping-method.png" alt="Choose Amazon as the shipping method" class="wp-image-354227" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-amazon-as-the-shipping-method.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/choose-amazon-as-the-shipping-method-300x150.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You‚Äôll now see options to enable Standard, Expedited, and Priority shipping. Just check the boxes next to the ones you want to offer at checkout.</p>



<p>For each shipping speed, you can apply a price adjustment, either as a fixed amount or a percentage. This gives you control over how much you want to charge customers based on the shipping method they select.</p>



<p>For example, you could offer <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-a-free-shipping-bar-in-woocommerce/" title="How to Add a Free Shipping Bar in WooCommerce (Step by Step)">Standard shipping for free</a>, charge a small fee for Expedited, and set a premium for Priority delivery ‚Äî depending on what works for your pricing strategy.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="361" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/set-shipping-rates-for-amazon-shipping-methods.png" alt="Set shipping rates for amazon shipping methods" class="wp-image-354228" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/set-shipping-rates-for-amazon-shipping-methods.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/set-shipping-rates-for-amazon-shipping-methods-300x159.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once you‚Äôre happy with the settings, click the &#8216;Create and save&#8217; button to activate Amazon shipping on your site.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-5-enable-amazon-fba-for-each-woocommerce-product">üõí Step 5: Enable Amazon FBA for Each WooCommerce Product</h4>



<p>Now that the plugin is connected and your shipping settings are in place, the final step is to enable FBA for each product you want Amazon to fulfill.</p>



<p>To do this, visit your <strong>Products ¬ª All Products</strong> page and click the &#8216;Edit&#8217; link for a product that you have already added to your Amazon inventory earlier.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="343" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/edit-product.png" alt="Click the Edit link for your preferred product" class="wp-image-327035" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/edit-product.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/edit-product-300x150.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open the product editor, where you have to scroll down to the &#8216;Product Data&#8217; section and look for the &#8216;Amazon Fulfillment&#8217; tab.</p>



<p>There, you‚Äôll see a checkbox labeled &#8216;Fulfill with Amazon FBA&#8217; ‚Äî go ahead and tick that box.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="368" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-fullfil-with-amazon-box.png" alt="Check fulfil with Amazon FBA box" class="wp-image-353373" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-fullfil-with-amazon-box.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/check-fullfil-with-amazon-box-300x162.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once selected, click the &#8216;Update&#8217; button to save your changes.</p>



<p>Now, repeat this process for each product you want Amazon to ship. Just make sure that the SKU in WooCommerce matches the SKU in your FBA inventory. If they don&#8217;t match, the order fulfillment will fail, or the sync won‚Äôt work properly.</p>



<p>Your products are now ready to be automatically fulfilled by Amazon whenever someone places an order in your WooCommerce store.</p>



