:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"woocommerce store";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"https://www.wpbeginner.com/?p=363512";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:692:"<p>Once, I missed sending a WooCommerce order notification and only found out because my customer reached out, upset. Relying on email alone often doesn‚Äôt cut it. Messages can get lost in spam, delayed, or ignored if shoppers don‚Äôt check their inboxes. Switching to WhatsApp made&#8230;&#160;<strong><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/send-woocommerce-order-notifications-to-whatsapp/">Read More &#187;</a></strong></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/send-woocommerce-order-notifications-to-whatsapp/">How I Send WooCommerce Order Notifications Straight to WhatsApp</a> first appeared on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com">WPBeginner</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Shahzad Saeed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:111132:"<p>Once, I missed sending a WooCommerce order notification and only found out because my customer reached out, upset. </p>



<p>Relying on email alone often doesn‚Äôt cut it. Messages can get lost in spam, delayed, or ignored if shoppers don‚Äôt check their inboxes.</p>



<p>Switching to WhatsApp made a big difference for me. Notifications arrive instantly, customers actually see them, and I can get real-time updates on every sale.</p>



<p>After testing several options, I‚Äôve narrowed it down to three reliable methods anyone can use. In this guide, I‚Äôll walk you through how to connect WhatsApp with WooCommerce, so you and your customers never miss an update again.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="385" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-send-woo-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-in-post.png" alt="How I Send WooCommerce Order Notifications Straight to WhatsApp " class="wp-image-363791" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-send-woo-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-in-post.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-send-woo-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-in-post-300x170.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-why-you-need-whatsapp-order-notifications">Why Set Up WooCommerce Order Notifications in WhatsApp?</h4>



<p>Relying only on email for WooCommerce order updates can cause issues. Emails can end up in spam, show up hours late, or just get lost in a busy inbox.</p>



<p>WhatsApp solves this by sending instant updates straight to your customer‚Äôs phone, so they never miss an important update.</p>



<p>Here&#8217;s a closer look at how connecting <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/woocommerce-tutorial-ultimate-guide/" title="WooCommerce Made Simple: A Step-by-Step Tutorial [+ Resources]">WooCommerce</a> and WhatsApp can be helpful:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>People check WhatsApp more.</strong>&nbsp;Many customers are on WhatsApp all day, while email gets ignored.</li>



<li><strong>Messages get read quickly.</strong>&nbsp;WhatsApp notifications are opened almost right away.</li>



<li><strong>Fewer customer questions.</strong>&nbsp;If shoppers get updates instantly, they don&#8217;t have to contact you for answers.</li>



<li><strong>Real-time updates build trust.</strong>&nbsp;Customers always know when their order is confirmed, <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-offer-shipment-tracking-in-woocommerce/" title="How to Offer Shipment Tracking in WooCommerce (Step by Step)">shipped</a>, or refunded.</li>
</ul>



<p>With WhatsApp, your messages actually reach customers, which means less confusion and a smoother shopping experience.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-which-method-should-i-choose">Which Method Should I Choose?</h5>



<p>In this guide, I‚Äôll cover 3 ways to send WooCommerce order notifications in WhatsApp. Here&#8217;s how I recommend choosing between them:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Method 1: PushEngage.</strong> Best for an all-in-one marketing platform. Send automated WhatsApp order updates to customers and your team, alongside <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-push-notification-software-for-websites-compared/" title="Best Web Push Notification Software (Compared)">push notifications</a>, cart recovery messages, and promotions.</li>



<li><strong>Method 2: Uncanny Automator.</strong> Set up custom ‚Äúrecipes‚Äù to trigger WhatsApp messages from WooCommerce events, with flexible automation options.</li>



<li><strong>Method 3: Wawp</strong>. A simple free option that connects to your personal or business phone (similar to WhatsApp Web). It&#8217;s ideal for testing or small stores, but your phone must remain on and connected to the internet for it to work.</li>
</ul>



<p>If you choose either method 1 or 2, you&#8217;ll also need to set up a WhatsApp Business account and message templates within WhatsApp. </p>



<p>Now, I&#8217;ll walk through each method step by step:</p>



<div class="wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents"><ul><li><a href="#aioseo-before-you-start-setup-a-whatsapp-business-account">Before You Start: Set Up Your WhatsApp Business Account (For Methods 1 &#x26; 2)</a><ul><li><a href="#aioseo-step-1-set-up-a-whatsapp-business-account">Step 1: Create a WhatsApp Business Account</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-2-get-a-permanent-access-token">Step 2: Get a Permanent Access Token</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-2-customize-message-templates-in-whatsapp-business-platform">Step 3: Customize Message Templates in WhatsApp Business Platform</a></li></ul></li><li><a href="#aioseo-method-1-send-woocommerce-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-with-pushengage">Method 1: Send WooCommerce Order Notifications with PushEngage (Multi-Channel Messaging)</a><ul><li><a href="#aioseo-step-3-install-and-activate-the-pushengage-plugin">Step 1: Install and Activate the PushEngage Plugin</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-4-connect-whatsapp-business-platform-account-to-pushengage">Step 2: Connect WhatsApp Business Platform Account to PushEngage</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-5-create-whatsapp-notification-automation-in-pushengage">Step 3: Create WhatsApp Notification Automation in PushEngage</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-6-test-your-whatsapp-notifications">Step 4: Test Your WhatsApp Notifications</a></li></ul></li><li><a href="#aioseo-method-2-send-woocommerce-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-automation-focused">Method 2: Send WooCommerce Order Notifications with Uncanny Automator (Automation-Focused)</a><ul><li><a href="#aioseo-step-3-install-and-activate-uncanny-automator">Step 1: Install and Activate Uncanny Automator</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-4-create-your-whatsapp-notification-automation-recipe">Step 2: Create Your WhatsApp Notification Automation Recipe</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-5-activate-and-test-your-automation">Step 3: Activate and Test Your Automation</a></li></ul></li><li><a href="#aioseo-method-3-send-woocommerce-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-free-option">Method 3: Send WooCommerce Order Notifications with a Free Plugin</a><ul><li><a href="#aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-wawp-plugin">Step 1: Install and Activate the Wawp Plugin</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-2-connect-your-wordrpess-site-and-your-wawp-account">Step 2: Connect Your WordPress Site and Your Wawp Account</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-3-create-automated-woocommerce-order-notifications">Step 3: Create Automated WooCommerce Order Notifications</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-step-4-test-your-automated-whatsapp-notification-setup">Step 4: Test Your Automated WhatsApp Notification Setup</a></li></ul></li><li><a href="#aioseo-bonus-tip-add-whatsapp-chatbox-and-share-buttons-in-wordpress">FAQs About Sending WooCommerce Order Notifications in WhatsApp</a></li><li><a href="#aioseo-further-reading-more-woocommerce-tutorials">Further Reading: More WooCommerce Tutorials</a></li></ul></div>



<p>Let&#8217;s get started.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-before-you-start-setup-a-whatsapp-business-account">Before You Start: Set Up Your WhatsApp Business Account (For Methods 1 &amp; 2)</h4>



<p>To connect your WooCommerce store with WhatsApp, you&#8217;ll need to set up a WhatsApp Business Suite account, generate a permanent token, and create WooCommerce message templates.</p>



<p>Here&#8217;s a quick checklist of what you‚Äôll need before you start:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>A Meta Business Suite account (or be ready to create one).</li>



<li>Admin access to that account.</li>



<li>A phone number that is <strong>not</strong> currently registered with a personal WhatsApp account. You&#8217;ll need this number exclusively for your business notifications.</li>
</ul>



<p>In the next sections, I‚Äôll guide you through each of these steps.</p>



<p></p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-1-set-up-a-whatsapp-business-account">Step 1: Create a WhatsApp Business Account</h5>



<p>If you don&#8217;t already have a Meta Business Suite account, you can create one on the <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Meta website">Meta website</a>.</p>



<p>Just click &#8216;Create a New Account&#8217; to sign up and complete the quick setup steps. Do note that you&#8217;ll need to verify your business information, which can take 1-2 business days.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p><strong>üí°</strong> <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The exact steps may vary slightly since Meta updates their interface from time to time, so don‚Äôt worry if things look a little different on your screen.</p>

</div>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="418" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-createanewaccount.png" alt="Creating a Meta Business account" class="wp-image-364676" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-createanewaccount.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-createanewaccount-300x184.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After creating your app, you‚Äôll land on the app dashboard.</p>



<p>Go ahead and click the &#8216;Create App&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="311" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp.png" alt="Creating an app" class="wp-image-364677" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-300x137.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will start the app setup wizard.</p>



<p>Here, simply fill in the &#8216;App name&#8217; and &#8216;App contact email&#8217; fields. This is for your reference only, but it&#8217;s helpful to have a clear, descriptive name.</p>



<p>After that, click the &#8216;Next&#8217; button to continue the process.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="336" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-appdetails.png" alt="Adding the app details" class="wp-image-364678" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-appdetails.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-appdetails-300x148.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, you&#8217;ll choose a use case.</p>



<p>As we want to send a WooCommerce order notification to WhatsApp, let&#8217;s select &#8216;Connect with customers through WhatsApp&#8217; and click &#8216;Next.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="461" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-usecases.png" alt="Choosing a use case" class="wp-image-364679" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-usecases.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-usecases-300x203.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After that, you‚Äôll need to link your business portfolio. Just click on the available option and click the &#8216;Next&#8217; button to move on.</p>



<p>If you don&#8217;t have one, you can just click on the &#8216;Create a business portfolio&#8217; link.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="287" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-business.png" alt="Choosing a business" class="wp-image-364681" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-business.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-business-300x127.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open a popup where you‚Äôll enter your first name, last name, and <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address-in-5-minutes-step-by-step/" title="How to Create a Free Business Email Address (in Just 5 Minutes)">business email address</a>.</p>



<p>Once done, click &#8216;Create Portfolio.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="348" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto.png" alt="Creating a business portfolio" class="wp-image-364680" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto-300x154.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Meta will then prompt you to verify your business portfolio.</p>



<p>Simply click &#8216;Start Verification&#8217; and follow the on-screen instructions.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="387" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto-startverification.png" alt="Click the Start Verification button" class="wp-image-364682" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto-startverification.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-createabusinessporto-startverification-300x171.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>The next step is to review requirements.</p>



<p>For WhatsApp-related apps, there typically won&#8217;t be any requirements identified. So you can go ahead and click the &#8216;Next&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="249" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-requirements.png" alt="Reviewing requirements" class="wp-image-364683" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-requirements.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-requirements-300x110.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>And for the last step, you‚Äôll see a summary of your new WhatsApp Notification app.</p>



<p>You can review everything and then click &#8216;Go to Dashboard.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="429" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-gotodashboard.png" alt="Click Go to Dashboard" class="wp-image-364684" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-gotodashboard.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metadeveloper-apps-createapp-gotodashboard-300x189.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>From the dashboard, you‚Äôll see a prompt to set up the WhatsApp Business Platform.</p>



<p>Here, you&#8217;ll want to click the &#8216;Customize the Connect with customers through WhatsApp use case&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="397" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize.png" alt="Customizing app in the app dashboard" class="wp-image-364686" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-300x175.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, you&#8217;ll see a prompt to start WhatsApp Business Platform configuration.</p>



<p>Go ahead and click the &#8216;Continue&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="470" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-continue.png" alt="Customizing WhatsApp business platform" class="wp-image-364687" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-continue.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-continue-300x207.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After that, you&#8217;ll see a WhatsApp Business Platform welcome message.</p>



<p>From here, you can click the &#8216;Start using the API&#8217; button to start.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="231" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup.png" alt="WhatsApp API Setup" class="wp-image-364688" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-300x102.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Then, in the &#8216;API Setup&#8217; panel, you&#8217;ll need to register your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-virtual-business-phone-number-apps-free-options/" title="7 Best Virtual Business Phone Number Apps (Free &amp; Paid)">phone number</a>. Otherwise, Meta will use a test number to send your messages.</p>



<p>Click to expand the dropdown and then hit the &#8216;+ Add phone number&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="362" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber.png" alt="Open dropdown to click Add phone number" class="wp-image-364689" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-300x160.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open a setup wizard for your WhatsApp configuration.</p>



<p>First, enter your business name, enter your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-make-a-small-business-website-step-by-step/" title="How to Make a Small Business Website ‚Äì Step by Step">business website address</a>, and choose your country. Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="355" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-businessinfo.png" alt="Adding business info" class="wp-image-364690" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-businessinfo.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-businessinfo-300x157.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After that, let&#8217;s set up your WhatsApp Business Platform account, which includes details like display name, timezone, category, and business description.</p>



<p>Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="434" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-wabusinessprofile.png" alt="Setting up WA Business Profile" class="wp-image-364691" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-wabusinessprofile.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-wabusinessprofile-300x191.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After that, go ahead and add your active phone number for WhatsApp.</p>



<p>Then, you can tick the radio button to confirm it through SMS or a phone call and click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="285" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-addnumber.png" alt="Entering your phone number" class="wp-image-364692" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-addnumber.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-addnumber-300x126.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In a few minutes, you should receive a verification code via SMS or phone call (depending on your choice in the previous step).</p>



<p>Once you have it, simply enter the 6-digit code in the field and click &#8216;Next.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="224" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-verifynumber.png" alt="Verifying the phone number" class="wp-image-364693" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-verifynumber.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-apisetup-addphonenumber-verifynumber-300x99.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Upon verification, you‚Äôll see a &#8216;Generate access token&#8217; button.</p>



<p>Go ahead and click on it.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="145" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken.png" alt="Generating temporary access token" class="wp-image-364694" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken-300x64.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the popup that appears, you&#8217;ll choose the WhatsApp account you want to give permissions to send notifications.</p>



<p>You&#8217;ll see the phone number you just registered and the test number that Meta provides. Let&#8217;s click on your registered phone number.</p>



<p>Meta will then ask you to grant your permission to send messages on your behalf.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="401" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken-choosewaaccount.png" alt="Choose a WhatsApp account" class="wp-image-364696" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken-choosewaaccount.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-customize-businessplatform-generate-accesstoken-choosewaaccount-300x177.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Meta will then take you back to the &#8216;API Setup&#8217; panel, where you can see your access token. Simply click the copy icon and store it somewhere safe, like a notepad.</p>



<p>Keep in mind, this token only lasts for 24 hours.</p>



<p>In addition to that, you&#8217;ll need to keep your &#8216;Phone number ID&#8217; and &#8216;WhatsApp Business Account ID&#8217; somewhere safe.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="412" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-copy-accesstoken-waid-phoneid.png" alt="Copy access token, WA ID, and phone number ID" class="wp-image-364697" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-copy-accesstoken-waid-phoneid.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-appdashboard-copy-accesstoken-waid-phoneid-300x182.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>With that done, you&#8217;ll get your WhatsApp Business Platform account.</p>



<p>You can access it through <a href="https://business.facebook.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Meta Business Suite">Meta Business Suite</a>.</p>



<p>In this account, you can create, manage, and track all your automated WhatsApp messages. Here&#8217;s what the <a href="https://business.facebook.com/latest/whatsapp_manager/overview/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="WhatsApp Manager interface">WhatsApp Manager interface</a> looks like:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="335" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager.png" alt="WhatsApp manager" class="wp-image-365012" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager-300x148.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-get-a-permanent-access-token">Step 2: Get a Permanent Access Token</h5>



<p>So far, we‚Äôve set things up so you can use WhatsApp on your WordPress site, but the access token you made earlier only works for 24 hours.</p>



<p>To ensure your automations can run 24/7, you‚Äôll need a <strong>permanent access token</strong>.</p>



<p>The way to get one is by creating a &#8216;System user&#8217; in your <a href="https://business.facebook.com/settings" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Business Settings">Meta Business Settings</a>. Think of a &#8216;System user&#8217; as a dedicated robot account that gives your tools (like PushEngage or Uncanny Automator) lasting permission to send messages on your behalf.</p>



<p>From your Business Settings, go ahead and select your business.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="289" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metabusinessmanager-business.png" alt="Select a business in Meta business manager" class="wp-image-366289" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metabusinessmanager-business.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/metabusinessmanager-business-300x128.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, let&#8217;s look at the left menu and go to &#8216;Settings.&#8217;</p>



<p>From here, you can click&nbsp;&#8216;System users&#8217; and hit the&nbsp;&#8216;Add&#8217;&nbsp;button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="314" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add.png" alt="Adding a system user in Meta" class="wp-image-366257" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add-300x139.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the popup that appears, go ahead and give your system user a name.</p>



<p>Then, select&nbsp;&#8216;Admin&#8217;&nbsp;as the role and click&nbsp;&#8216;Create system user.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="384" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add-createsystemuser.png" alt="Create system user name and role" class="wp-image-366258" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add-createsystemuser.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-add-createsystemuser-300x169.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once that‚Äôs done, you‚Äôll be back on the &#8216;System users&#8217; page.</p>



<p>Here, click on the three-dot button on the right and select &#8216;Assign Assets.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="213" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-more-assignassets.png" alt="Assigning assets in Meta" class="wp-image-366286" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-more-assignassets.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-more-assignassets-300x94.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the popup that appears, you&#8217;ll need to assign permissions.</p>



<p>To do this, you can click &#8216;Apps,&#8217; select your asset, and switch the &#8216;Manage app&#8217; on in the &#8216;Full control&#8217; section.</p>



<p>With that done, go ahead and click the &#8216;Assign assets&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="409" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assignassets-apps-wanotif-fullcontrol.png" alt="Enabling full control in a Meta asset" class="wp-image-366260" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assignassets-apps-wanotif-fullcontrol.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assignassets-apps-wanotif-fullcontrol-300x180.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Meta will then ask you to review and accept their non-discrimination policy.</p>



<p>Basically, this tells you that you agree not to use Facebook‚Äôs advertising tools for anything that discriminates against people based on things like race, religion, gender, age, or other protected characteristics.</p>



<p>It‚Äôs just their way to make sure everyone is treated fairly and that ads follow the law.</p>



<p>Once granted, you&#8217;ll see the &#8216;Asset assigned&#8217; message. Simply click the &#8216;Done&#8217; button or &#8216;X&#8217; to close this popup.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="466" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assetassigned.png" alt="Assets assigned message in Meta" class="wp-image-366261" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assetassigned.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-assetassigned-300x206.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will take you back to the &#8216;System users&#8217; page.</p>



<p>And you should now see a&nbsp;&#8216;Generate Token&#8217;&nbsp;button in your system user. Let&#8217;s click on that.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="197" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken.png" alt="Generating token in System users" class="wp-image-366262" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-300x87.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the window that pops up, you&#8217;ll see a 4-step setup wizard for your permanent token.</p>



<p>From here, you can select your app from the dropdown menu and then click the &#8216;Next&#8217; button to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="477" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-selectapp.png" alt="Selecting app to generate permanent token" class="wp-image-366267" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-selectapp.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-selectapp-300x210.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You can then set when the token should expire.</p>



<p>Make sure to choose &#8216;Never&#8217; and click on &#8216;Next.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="472" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-setexpiration-never.png" alt="Setting up token expiration to never" class="wp-image-366268" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-setexpiration-never.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-setexpiration-never-300x208.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>The next step is to assign permissions.</p>



<p>You‚Äôll see a list of options, and you&#8217;ll want to check the boxes for:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>whatsapp_business_management</li>



<li>whatsapp_business_messaging</li>
</ul>



<p>This lets your system user manage your WhatsApp business account and send messages on your behalf. Basically, you‚Äôre giving the necessary access so everything works smoothly.</p>



<p>Once you‚Äôve checked those boxes, just click the&nbsp;&#8216;Next&#8217;&nbsp;button to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="474" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-assignpermissions.png" alt="Assigning permissions for the token" class="wp-image-366265" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-assignpermissions.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-assignpermissions-300x209.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the last step, you&#8217;ll see your permanent token.</p>



<p>Just click the &#8216;Copy&#8217; button and &#8216;Done&#8217; to finish this up.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="478" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-done.png" alt="Permanent token generated" class="wp-image-366266" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-done.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-settings-systemusers-generatetoken-done-300x211.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>With that done, I recommend storing this somewhere safe, like a <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/what-is-the-best-way-to-manage-passwords-for-wordpress-beginners/" title="How to Easily and Securely Manage Passwords (Beginner‚Äôs Guide)">password manager</a>.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-customize-message-templates-in-whatsapp-business-platform">Step 3: Customize Message Templates in WhatsApp Business Platform</h5>



<p>Before you go on, you&#8217;ll need to create a few automated order messages for your app.</p>



<p>By default, your WhatsApp Business Platform account comes with a <code>hello_world</code> template. It‚Äôs fine for testing, but it‚Äôs not very useful for real order notifications.</p>



<p>That‚Äôs why we‚Äôll add new templates tailored to your store. This way, your WhatsApp notifications are more relevant, branded, and effective.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-orange">

<p>üí° <strong>Important:</strong> Both <a href="https://pushengage.com" target="_blank" title="PushEngage - Best Web Push Notification Software">PushEngage</a> and <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/uncanny-automator-2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Uncanny Automator">Uncanny Automator</a> pull message templates directly from your WhatsApp Business Platform account. If you skip this step, you‚Äôll only be able to use the basic <code>hello_world</code> template for automation.</p>

</div>


<p>Inside your WhatsApp Manager, head over to the &#8216;Message templates&#8217; section.</p>



<p>Here, you‚Äôll find the &#8216;Template library,&#8217; which includes pre-made templates that you can customize and activate right away.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="326" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager-messagetemplates-templatelibrary.png" alt="Template library in WhatsApp manager" class="wp-image-365013" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager-messagetemplates-templatelibrary.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsappmanager-messagetemplates-templatelibrary-300x144.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>For this tutorial, though, let‚Äôs create one from scratch. This gives you full control to match <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-build-your-personal-brand-using-wordpress/" title="How to Build Your Personal Brand Using WordPress">your brand</a> voice and set up the right dynamic tags.</p>



<p>Just go to the &#8216;Message templates&#8217; section and click the &#8216;Create Template&#8217; button to open the text editor.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="305" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-messagetemplates-createtemplate.png" alt="Creating template in Meta" class="wp-image-364719" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-messagetemplates-createtemplate.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/meta-messagetemplates-createtemplate-300x135.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, you‚Äôll need to pick a template type:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Marketing</strong> ‚Äì for promotions, sales, or offers.</li>



<li><strong>Utility</strong> ‚Äì for order updates, shipping info, or other customer updates.</li>



<li><strong>Authentication</strong> ‚Äì for login codes or password resets.</li>
</ul>



<p>For order notifications, let&#8217;s use the &#8216;Utility&#8217; template since these messages provide customers with order information, not promotions or login details.</p>



<p>Then, there are the &#8216;Default&#8217; and &#8216;Calling permission request&#8217; options:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Default</strong> ‚Äì Lets you send messages about an existing order or customer account. This is the option most <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/woocommerce-tutorial-ultimate-guide/" title="WooCommerce Made Simple: A Step-by-Step Tutorial [+ Resources]">WooCommerce</a> stores will use.</li>



<li><strong>Calling permission request</strong> ‚Äì Asks customers if you can call them on WhatsApp, which usually isn‚Äôt needed for order notifications.</li>
</ul>



<p>For this setup, let&#8217;s click &#8216;Default&#8217; since we only need to send order updates. Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to continue.</p>



