<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="315" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew.png" alt="The Add New Plugin submenu under Plugins in the WordPress admin area" class="wp-image-332530" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew-300x139.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Then, search for &#8220;Uncanny Automator,&#8221; click the &#8216;Install Now&#8217; in the search result, then click &#8216;Activate&#8217; when it appears.</p>



<p>You can see our guide on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/" title="How to Install a WordPress Plugin ‚Äì Step by Step for Beginners">how to install a WordPress plugin</a> for step-by-step instructions.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="394" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/install-uncanny-automator-free-plugin.jpg" alt="Install Uncanny Automator free plugin" class="wp-image-339613" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/install-uncanny-automator-free-plugin.jpg 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/install-uncanny-automator-free-plugin-300x174.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After activation, you&#8217;ll see a new &#8216;Automator&#8217; menu in your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/13-plugins-and-tips-to-improve-wordpress-admin-area/" title="Plugins and Tips to Improve WordPress Admin Area">WordPress admin area</a>.</p>



<p>Click on it and follow the setup wizard to register your account and claim your free credits.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="381" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/ua-return-to-dashboard.png" alt="The Uncanny Automator setup wizard" class="wp-image-356574" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/ua-return-to-dashboard.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/ua-return-to-dashboard-300x168.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>To connect Uncanny Automator with WhatsApp, go to <strong>Automator ¬ª Settings ¬ª App Integrations ¬ª WhatsApp</strong>.</p>



<p>Then, you can go ahead and click &#8216;Connect WhatsApp account.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="391" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect.png" alt="Connecting Uncanny Automator to WhatsApp" class="wp-image-364879" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect-300x173.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>From here, you can paste in your permanent token, phone number ID, and WhatsApp Business Account ID from the Meta dashboard.</p>



<p>And once again, click on the &#8216;Connect WhatsApp account&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="321" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-form-connect.png" alt="Connecting WhatsApp to Uncanny Automator" class="wp-image-364877" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-form-connect.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-form-connect-300x142.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After a few seconds, you&#8217;ll get a success message.</p>



<p>And here&#8217;s what it looks like:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="367" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect-successful.png" alt="Successful WhatsApp and Uncanny Automator integration" class="wp-image-364881" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect-successful.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-appintegrations-whatsapp-connect-successful-300x162.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-4-create-your-whatsapp-notification-automation-recipe">Step 2: Create Your WhatsApp Notification Automation Recipe</h5>



<p>Automator uses &#8220;recipes&#8221; to describe automations. Think of them like &#8220;if-then rules&#8221; that connect different parts of your website. Each recipe has triggers (what starts the automation) and actions (what happens as a result).</p>



<p>To create your automation recipe, let&#8217;s first navigate to <strong>Automator ¬ª Add new recipe</strong> in your WordPress dashboard.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="411" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/automator-addnewrecipe.png" alt="Add new recipe in Automator" class="wp-image-361042" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/automator-addnewrecipe.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/automator-addnewrecipe-300x181.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the popup that appears, you&#8217;ll see a modal asking what type of recipe you want to create.</p>



<p>Let&#8217;s choose &#8216;Everyone&#8217; as the recipe type and click &#8216;Confirm.&#8217;</p>



<p>This way, your automation will work for both customers with accounts and those who <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-create-faster-checkout-in-woocommerce/" title="How to Create Faster Checkout in WooCommerce (Expert Tips)">check out as guests</a>. Uncanny Automator can pull the phone number directly from the order details, so notifications will be sent to all purchasers.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="387" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/uncanny-automator-everyone.png" alt="Creating an automated recipe for all users" class="wp-image-160551" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/uncanny-automator-everyone.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/uncanny-automator-everyone-300x171.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the recipe editor, you can go ahead and give your recipe a descriptive name like &#8220;WhatsApp Notifications for WooCommerce Orders.&#8221; Clear naming helps a lot when you have multiple recipes running.</p>



<p>After that, you can scroll down to set up what event should start your WhatsApp notification.</p>



<p>Automator has dozens of WooCommerce triggers to choose from. In the &#8216;Trigger&#8217; panel, select &#8216;WooCommerce&#8217; (or Woo) from the list of available integrations.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="453" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo.png" alt="Choosing WooCommerce as trigger" class="wp-image-364882" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-300x200.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the dropdown, you&#8217;ll see various WooCommerce events you can use as triggers.</p>



<p>Let&#8217;s choose &#8216;A user purchases a product.&#8217; This trigger fires when someone successfully completes their purchase.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="439" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-auserpurchaseaproduct.png" alt="A user purchases a product trigger" class="wp-image-364883" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-auserpurchaseaproduct.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-auserpurchaseaproduct-300x194.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>If you have the Pro version, you&#8217;ll get more options.</p>



<p>For example, you can choose a more specific trigger like &#8220;A user completes, pays, and lands on a <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-easily-create-custom-woocommerce-thank-you-pages/" title="How to Easily Create Custom WooCommerce Thank You Pages">thank-you page</a> for a variable product with a variation selected.&#8221;</p>



<p>After that, you can set the trigger condition to &#8216;pays for&#8217; so it only runs when payment is actually processed. Then, you can click the &#8216;Save&#8217; button to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="422" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-triggerconditions.png" alt="Setting up the trigger condition as pays for" class="wp-image-364884" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-triggerconditions.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-triggerconditions-300x186.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Then, you&#8217;ll need to specify your product selection.</p>



<p>You can choose &#8216;Any product,&#8217; unless you only want notifications for specific items. Don&#8217;t forget to click &#8216;Save.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="373" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-product.png" alt="Specifying which products to fire trigger" class="wp-image-364885" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-product.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-trigger-woo-product-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>The next step is to set up an action. This is what happens after your trigger fires. In other words, this is where you&#8217;ll configure the actual WhatsApp message.</p>



<p>To start, click the &#8216;Add action&#8217; button in the &#8216;Actions&#8217; panel.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="416" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-addaction.png" alt="Adding an action" class="wp-image-364887" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-addaction.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-addaction-300x184.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Then, you can select &#8216;WhatsApp&#8217; from the integration list.</p>



<p>You&#8217;ll also notice that there are plenty of other integrations available with Uncanny Automator, including OptinMonster and <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-create-a-custom-airtable-form-in-wordpress/" title="How to Create a Custom Airtable Form in WordPress (Easy Way)">Airtable</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="439" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp.png" alt="Selecting WhatsApp integration for action" class="wp-image-364888" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-300x194.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Now, you should see different WhatsApp actions available.</p>



<p>Here, you can choose &#8216;Send a WhatsApp message template&#8217; for first-time notifications that need to follow WhatsApp&#8217;s template requirements.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="318" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-sendmessagetemplates.png" alt="Choosing Send a WhatsApp message template for action" class="wp-image-364889" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-sendmessagetemplates.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-sendmessagetemplates-300x140.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Make sure to pick the template that you created in the WhatsApp Manager dashboard. In my example, it&#8217;s called &#8216;new_order_notification&#8217;. </p>



<p>The &#8216;Send a WhatsApp message to a number&#8217; method works better for customers who have already opted in to receive messages.</p>



<p>Remember to click the &#8216;Save&#8217; button when it appears.</p>



<p>In the phone number field, you can use Automator&#8217;s token system to pull the customer&#8217;s billing phone from their order. </p>



<p>Just click the asterisk icon, select the &#8216;Billing phone&#8217; token from <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/woocommerce-tutorial-ultimate-guide/" title="WooCommerce Made Simple: A Step-by-Step Tutorial [+ Resources]">WooCommerce</a>, and click &#8216;Save.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="348" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-phonenumber-asterisk-billingphone.png" alt="Choosing the Billing Phone dynamic tag" class="wp-image-364890" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-phonenumber-asterisk-billingphone.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-actions-whatsapp-phonenumber-asterisk-billingphone-300x154.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-5-activate-and-test-your-automation">Step 3: Activate and Test Your Automation</h5>



<p>Now, you can activate your recipe, and Automator makes this easy with their draft and live modes.</p>



<p>To activate your automated WhatsApp notification recipes, you can toggle from &#8216;Draft&#8217; to &#8216;Live&#8217; using the switch at the top of the recipe page.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="382" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-live.png" alt="Making Uncanny Automator recipe live" class="wp-image-364892" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-live.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-recipe-whatsapp-live-300x169.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Now, you can place a test order on your online store using your own phone number as the customer contact. Make sure you complete the entire <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-customize-woocommerce-checkout-page/" title="How to Customize WooCommerce Checkout Page (The Easy Way)">WooCommerce checkout</a> process, including payment.</p>



<p>Within a few minutes, you should receive a WhatsApp notification with all the dynamic tokens displaying the correct information from your test order.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="412" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-new-order-notification.png" alt="WhatsApp new order notification" class="wp-image-365147" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-new-order-notification.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-new-order-notification-300x182.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You can also head to your WooCommerce dashboard and manually change the test order‚Äôs status from ‚ÄòProcessing‚Äô to ‚ÄòCompleted‚Äô.</p>



<p>This will trigger any extra notifications you‚Äôve configured.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="216" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-order-complete-notification.png" alt="WhatsApp order complete notification" class="wp-image-365148" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-order-complete-notification.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/whatsapp-order-complete-notification-300x95.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>That&#8217;s all!</p>



<p>And to monitor all your automation activity, you can go to the <strong>Automator ¬ª Logs</strong> section, which shows you exactly when recipes run and whether they succeed or cause errors.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="375" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-logs-recipes.png" alt="The logs in Uncanny Automator" class="wp-image-365151" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-logs-recipes.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/uncanny-logs-recipes-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-method-3-send-woocommerce-order-notifications-in-whatsapp-free-option">Method 3: Send WooCommerce Order Notifications with a Free Plugin</h4>



<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/automation-web-platform/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Wawp">Wawp</a> is a lightweight WhatsApp notification plugin designed for simplicity and quick setup. Its main advantage is that it <strong>doesn‚Äôt require a full Meta Business API setup</strong>, making it ideal for small <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-start-an-online-store/" title="How to Start an Online Store (Step by Step for Beginners)">online stores</a> or anyone testing WhatsApp notifications.</p>


<div class="wpb-alert style-blue">

<p><strong>üí° Heads up:</strong> Since this method uses your phone to send messages, it&#8217;s important that your phone stays charged, turned on, and connected to the internet. If your phone goes offline, notifications will stop sending until it reconnects.</p>

</div>


<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-wawp-plugin">Step 1: Install and Activate the Wawp Plugin</h5>



<p>Before installing the plugin, you need to go to the <a href="https://wawp.net/signup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Wawp website">Wawp website</a> and follow the signup process for a free account.</p>



<p>Start by clicking the &#8216;Start Free Forever&#8217; button, filling in your account details, and verifying your WhatsApp number.</p>



<p>The free plan lets you send up to 50 messages per month, so you can experiment with order updates without any upfront cost. When you‚Äôre ready, it‚Äôs easy to upgrade or move to a more advanced solution like PushEngage or Uncanny Automator. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="360" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-site.png" alt="Wawp's site" class="wp-image-364818" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-site.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-site-300x159.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In your account dashboard, you&#8217;ll see the setup wizard.</p>



<p>The first thing to do here is click the &#8216;Connect Now&#8217; button to launch the wizard.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="344" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-connectnow.png" alt="Connect now button" class="wp-image-364819" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-connectnow.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-connectnow-300x152.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will take you to the &#8216;Linked Numbers&#8217; panel, where Wawp will prompt you to create a new instance.</p>



<p>An instance is like a workspace that links your WhatsApp number to Wawp. Think of it as the bridge between your Wawp account and your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/" title="How to Make a WordPress Website (Ultimate Guide)">WordPress website</a>. Without it, your store can‚Äôt send or receive WhatsApp messages.</p>



<p>Go ahead and click on the &#8216;Create New Instance&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="258" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance.png" alt="Creating new instance" class="wp-image-364820" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance-300x114.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Here&#8217;s where Wawp&#8217;s approach differs significantly from the other methods. Instead of a complex API setup, you simply scan a QR code with your phone.</p>



<p>Just click the &#8216;Scan QR&#8217; button, and in your phone, tap &#8216;Link a Device&#8217; and use your phone&#8217;s camera to scan the QR code from your computer screen.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="237" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance-scanqr.png" alt="Scanning QR to create new instance" class="wp-image-364821" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance-scanqr.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-setup-createnewinstance-scanqr-300x105.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once connected, Wawp will show you the &#8216;Connected&#8217; label and generate the &#8216;Instance ID&#8217; for your account automatically.</p>



<p>On this page, you can also see your &#8216;Access Token.&#8217;</p>



<p>Let&#8217;s copy both pieces of information, as you&#8217;ll need them in step 2.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="273" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-accesstoken-instanceid.png" alt="Copying access token and instance id" class="wp-image-364822" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-accesstoken-instanceid.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-accesstoken-instanceid-300x120.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>With that done, you can start installing the Wawp plugin.</p>



<p>In your WordPress dashboard, go to <strong>Plugins ¬ª Add New</strong>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="315" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew.png" alt="The Add New Plugin submenu under Plugins in the WordPress admin area" class="wp-image-332530" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/wp-plugins-addnew-300x139.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, simply use the search bar to find the Wawp plugin.</p>



<p>When you see the plugin in the search results, click the &#8216;Install Now&#8217; button. Then, once again, on &#8216;Activate&#8217; to complete the process.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="401" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wp-plugin-addplugin-wawp.png" alt="Installing Wawp in WordPress" class="wp-image-364843" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wp-plugin-addplugin-wawp.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wp-plugin-addplugin-wawp-300x177.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



