<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-connect-your-wordrpess-site-and-your-wawp-account">Step 2: Connect Your WordPress Site and Your Wawp Account</h5>



<p>Now that you have Wawp installed on your site, let&#8217;s connect both platforms.</p>



<p>From your dashboard, you&#8217;ll want to navigate to <strong>Wawp <strong>¬ª</strong> Sender Settings</strong>. Then, in the &#8216;Connect your WhatsApp&#8217; section, go ahead and click &#8216;+ Add Manually.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="229" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-manualconnection.png" alt="Choosing manual connection for Wawp and WordPress" class="wp-image-364827" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-manualconnection.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-manualconnection-300x101.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open a popup where you can fill in your instance details.</p>



<p>Simply copy and paste your instance name, instance ID, and access token into the relevant fields. After that, click &#8216;Save&#8217; to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="362" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-addinstancemanually.png" alt="Connecting an instance in WordPress" class="wp-image-364828" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-addinstancemanually.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-addinstancemanually-300x160.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will redirect you to the &#8216;Sender Settings&#8217; panel.</p>



<p>In the &#8216;Connected Numbers&#8217; section, you should be able to see your instance added. The &#8216;Online&#8217; connection status indicates that the link is successful.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="251" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-online.png" alt="Instance connected" class="wp-image-364829" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-online.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-sendersettings-whatsappweb-online-300x111.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-3-create-automated-woocommerce-order-notifications">Step 3: Create Automated WooCommerce Order Notifications</h5>



<p>By now, you&#8217;re ready to create your WooCommerce order notifications.</p>



<p>In the Wawp plugin settings, look for the &#8216;Notifications Builder&#8217; section and click &#8216;+ New Notification.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="359" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification.png" alt="Adding new notification in Wawp" class="wp-image-364832" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-300x158.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You&#8217;ll then see different WooCommerce events listed in &#8216;Trigger Events.&#8217;</p>



<p>They include &#8216;Order Status: Processing,&#8217; &#8216;Order Status: Completed,&#8217; &#8216;Order Status: Failed,&#8217; and so on. </p>



<p>For the first notification, let&#8217;s choose &#8216;Processing.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="357" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-triggerevent.png" alt="WooCommerce trigger events" class="wp-image-364833" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-triggerevent.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-triggerevent-300x158.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This will open the notification template customization panel, where you can adjust the following settings:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Waiting Time</strong> ‚Äì Choose how long to wait before the notification is sent: instant or after a few minutes delay.</li>



<li><strong>Send Via</strong> ‚Äì Select the delivery channel: WhatsApp, email, or both. By default, this is set to WhatsApp.</li>



<li><strong>Send To</strong> ‚Äì Decide who should receive the message: the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/wordpress-user-roles-and-permissions/" title="Beginner‚Äôs Guide to WordPress User Roles and Permissions">user</a>, the admin, or both.</li>
</ul>



<p>For example, my setup is: &#8216;Instant&#8217; for Waiting Time, &#8216;WhatsApp&#8217; for Send Via, and &#8216;User&#8217; for Send To.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="368" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-sendto.png" alt="Send to options" class="wp-image-364834" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-sendto.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-sendto-300x162.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>If you scroll further down this panel, you‚Äôll find some additional options. For instance, you can choose to include the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-create-a-woocommerce-product-image-gallery-step-by-step/" title="How to Create a WooCommerce Product Image Gallery (Step by Step)">product image</a> in your WhatsApp notifications.</p>



<p>You‚Äôll also see a few WooCommerce filters that let you control exactly when messages are sent:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-country-restriction-for-woocommerce-products/" title="How to Add Country Restriction for WooCommerce Products">Country Filter</a>:</strong> Send or exclude messages based on the customer‚Äôs billing country.</li>



<li><strong>Product Filter:</strong> Target specific products by choosing whether to send or not send messages for them.</li>



<li><strong>Payment Gateway Filter:</strong> Decide which payment methods, like Stripe, bank transfer, check, or COD, should trigger a notification.</li>
</ul>



<p>You can tweak these filters to fit your store‚Äôs workflow and customer base.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="394" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-productimage-filter.png" alt="Include product images and filters" class="wp-image-364835" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-productimage-filter.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-productimage-filter-300x174.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Next, you might want to edit the basic message template.</p>



<p>I personally always customize the message to match how I communicate with customers. Personal touches make a big difference in customer service. </p>



<p>You can scroll up this panel and click the pencil icon to edit the message template. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="295" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-edittemplate.png" alt="The Edit Template button in Wawp" class="wp-image-364836" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-edittemplate.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-edittemplate-300x130.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>In the popup that appears, you can type your custom message into the text field.</p>



<p>You might also notice that Wawp supports dynamic tags like {Order_ID}, {Display_Name}, and {Order_Total}. These tags automatically fill in information from each specific order.</p>



<p>So, for example, you might write:</p>



<p>&#8220;<em>Hello {display_name}, thanks for shopping with {site_title}!</em><br><em>We‚Äôve received your order #{order_id} and it‚Äôs now being processed. üõí&nbsp;</em><br><em>Have questions? Just reply to this message and our team will be happy to help! ‚ú®&nbsp;</em>&#8220;</p>



<p>Don&#8217;t forget to click &#8216;Finish &amp; Save&#8217; to apply your custom WhatsApp message.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="427" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-editmessage-dynamicvariables.png" alt="Dynamic tags in Wawp" class="wp-image-364837" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-editmessage-dynamicvariables.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-newnotification-editmessage-dynamicvariables-300x188.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You can repeat this process for all the order notifications you want to send through WhatsApp. For most stores, I think new order and order complete notifications are a good start.</p>



<p>Once you&#8217;re finished with your automated WhatsApp notifications, you can see them all listed in your Wawp&#8217;s notification builders like this:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="288" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-notifications-processing-completed.png" alt="WhatsApp order notifications in Wawp" class="wp-image-364840" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-notifications-processing-completed.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wawp-notificationsbuilder-notifications-processing-completed-300x127.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



